- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper deals with modeling cyber-physical systems and constraining the model with rules. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is relevant as the paper focuses on reducing energy consumption and CO2 emissions in buildings. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is possible as the paper mentions using techniques from the modeling domain to detect inefficiencies. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also possible as the paper presents a domain-specific language for modeling buildings and technical facilities.
